The paper discusses a technique for Gibbs sampling on factor graphs, which is commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses a specific application in natural language processing, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new graph property, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
